SIMPLE: meditation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Meditation
<hw>Med`i*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>meditacioun</ets>, F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧ditation</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>meditatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of meditating;
close or continued thought; the turning or revolving of a subject in the
mind; serious contemplation; reflection; musing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let the words of my mouth and the <qex>meditation</qex> of my
heart be acceptable in thy sight.</q> <rj><qau>Ps. xix.
14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Thought; -- without regard to kind.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With wings as swift⟦br⟧
As <qex>meditation</qex> or the thoughts of love.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meditatist</ent>⟦br⟧
